#Chef is watching a football match. The current score is A:B, that is, team 1 has scored A goals and team 2 has scored B goals. Chef wonders if it is possible for the score to become 
C:D at a later point in the game (i.e. team 1 has scored C goals and team 2 has scored D goals). Can you help Chef by answering his question?



t=int(input())
for i in range(t):
    A,B=map(int,input().split())
    C,D=map(int,input().split())
    if(C>=A and D>=B):
        print("POSSIBLE")
    else:
        print("IMPOSSIBLE")
